Star actor, Adebayo Salami, has appreciated God and his family on his 70th birthday. The veteran took to his official Instagram account to celebrate his achievements with a picture. He wrote: “At 70, life makes more meaning to me through the blessings of family and endearing legacies of my career. Alhamdulilahi for the grace of this day.”   Trying to destroy beautiful relationship evil – Made…     Olu-Omo’s son: One wife enough for men     Dancer Korra accuses estranged husband of withdrawing $5,000   Several film stars have taken to the comment section to shower eulogies and encomiums on the fine actor and producer. Adebayo Salami popularly known by his stage name Oga Bello, is a veteran actor, filmmaker, movie producer and director.